First, I'd check if the flashlight bulb workin'. If not, I'd replace it. If the bulb alright, then I'd check the batteries. Dead or weak batteries be the reason a flashlight ain't workin' half the time. If the batteries cool, I'd check the battery part for rust. Rust mess up the flow of electricity from the batteries to the bulb.

Next, I'd check the flashlight switch.  A messed-up switch stop the electricity flow. I'd also check the wires inside. If any wires loose or broke, I'd solder 'em back. If the flashlight still ain't workin' after all that, it might be somethin' serious, and I'd take it to somebody who knows what they doin'.
